        "executive_summary": "Monterey Office delivered a composite performance score of 54 out of 100 (where 50 represents the network average) in March 2026, demonstrating solid operational fundamentals alongside emerging capacity pressures. Scheduler Compliance reached 86.0% and Chair Utilization climbed to 98.0%, both aligning with company averages of 86.04% and 97.98% respectively, while average patient delay of 15.5 minutes matched the company benchmark of 15.46 minutes. However, treatments extending past closing time rose to 4.4 per day in March from 2.5 in February, a pattern worth understanding as the clinic scales.",
        "highlights": [
          "Monterey's Chair Utilization improved from 87.0% in February to 98.0% in March\u2014a 12.7-percentage-point gain that reflects strong capacity deployment and recovery from prior underutilization. Scheduler Compliance advanced from 81.1% in February to 86.0% in March, a 6.0-percentage-point improvement that now positions the clinic at parity with the company average of 86.04%, signaling tighter adherence to iOptimize recommendations."
