        "concerns": [
          "We noticed that treatments running past closing time increased from 2.5 per day in February to 4.4 in March\u2014a 74.4% rise\u2014while average delay climbed from 13.5 minutes to 15.5 minutes over the same period. Both metrics show consistent deterioration over the three-month trend window (3-month averages: 3.1 treatments past close, 14.2-minute delay), suggesting the clinic's expanded Chair Utilization and elevated Nurse Utilization (which rose from 80.3% to 87.1%, a meaningful 8.4-percentage-point gain) may be creating scheduling strain. One area worth exploring together is whether current staffing and block-scheduling practices can absorb the recent volume gains without systematically pushing appointments into overtime."
        ],
        "recommendations": [
          "We recommend Monterey conduct a brief operational review of treatment-block scheduling to understand whether the leap in chair utilization is creating a mismatch between appointment duration estimates and actual treatment times. A focused conversation with the scheduling and nursing teams\u2014examining whether iOptimize recommendations are being followed at peak hours and whether nurse-to-patient ratios during peak windows are sustainable\u2014could surface quick wins to bring treatments past closing back toward zero while preserving the strong utilization gains."
        ]
